{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17651398","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17651398"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:24:06+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:24:06+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18459"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18459","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18459"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.04,0,0.96,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11188"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75381"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11188"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18459"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60890"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5663"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25953"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25990"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75381","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75381"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA healthcare provider is discussing treatment options with an Indigenous patient who speaks English as a second language. The provider needs to obtain informed consent for a surgical procedure.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the key requirement for obtaining valid informed consent in this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Obtaining written consent in English only","Proceeding with treatment if the patient appears to understand","Documenting consent in the medical record without translation","Providing information in a culturally and linguistically appropriate manner","Having a family member translate the information"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach involves \u003Cstrong\u003Eproviding information in a culturally and linguistically appropriate manner\u003C/strong\u003E. This ensures the patient can make an informed decision about their healthcare while respecting their cultural and linguistic background. This may include using qualified interpreters and culturally appropriate resources.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObtaining written consent in English only\u003C/strong\u003E does not ensure true understanding and fails to address language barriers.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProceeding with treatment if the patient appears to understand\u003C/strong\u003E is insufficient as apparent understanding does not guarantee actual comprehension of the procedure and its risks.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocumenting consent in the medical record without translation\u003C/strong\u003E fails to address the patient\u0027s right to receive information in an understandable format.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHaving a family member translate the information\u003C/strong\u003E is inappropriate as family members may lack the medical knowledge to accurately translate complex information and their presence may influence the patient\u0027s decision-making.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers have a responsibility to ensure that consent is truly informed, which includes addressing any cultural or linguistic barriers to understanding.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The concept of informed consent requires that patients receive adequate information about their condition, treatment options, and potential risks.","Healthcare providers must ensure information is communicated in a culturally appropriate way for Indigenous patients.","Language barriers and cultural differences can impact the informed consent process for Indigenous patients."],"references":["Chauhan A, Walpola RL, Manias E, Seale H, Walton M, Wilson C, Smith AB, Li J, Harrison R. How do health services engage culturally and linguistically diverse consumers? An analysis of consumer engagement frameworks in Australia. Health Expect. 2021 Oct;24(5):1747-1762. doi: 10.1111/hex.13315. Epub 2021 Jul 15. PMID: 34264537; PMCID: PMC8483202."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60890"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18459"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60890","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60890"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T18:38:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-29T18:40:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11188"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75381"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/ta